        <briefdescription>
<para>This function sends a command to ASUFW to perform LMS signature verification on the provided message using the given LMS public key. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ClientParamsPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the XAsu_ClientParams structure which holds the client input parameters. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>LmsParamsPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to <ref refid="struct_x_asu___lms_hss_sign_verify_params" kindref="compound">XAsu_LmsHssSignVerifyParams</ref> structure which holds the parameters for LMS signature verification.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS, if IPI request to ASU is sent successfully.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XASU_INVALID_ARGUMENT, if any argument is invalid.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XASU_QUEUE_FULL, if Queue buffer is full.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE, if sending an IPI request to ASU fails.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XASU_INVALID_UNIQUE_ID, if received Queue ID is invalid. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Validate input parameters.</para><para>Generate a unique ID and register the callback function.</para><para>Set the command ID based on the selected SHA type.</para><para>Create command header.</para><para>Update request buffer and send an IPI request to ASU. </para>        </inbodydescription>
